{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PLAN REVIEW · CONTAINER · [G4] Child consistency — pairing (parent 6f2d ⟶ child 4024 WS-DOC), cross-checked against the complete authoritative 2-child roster [WS-DOC (4024) + WS-EVAL-EXISTING (b4af)] — VERDICT: 1 finding (ordering violation). Re-affirms the prior G4 recording on this pairing after a fresh full 7-mode re-check.\n\n7-mode audit (CLEAN except ordering):\n- Implicit shared state — CLEAN. Both children touch the eval seam, but the division is BUILD (b4af) vs DOCUMENT (4024); WS-DOC reads what WS-EVAL-EXISTING produces (\"reflects WS-EVAL-EXISTING as built\"). No undeclared shared mutable artifact.\n- Conflicting assumptions — CLEAN. The two-tier eval model is described identically on both sides: zero-cost deterministic gate every PR + LLM-judge tier off the PR critical path (workflow_dispatch + weekly schedule, non-blocking, response-cached, concurrency-capped, fork-safe, spend-cap-guided). WS-DOC AC4 ≡ b4af AC4/AC5; no contradiction.\n- Scope overlap — CLEAN. Document the seam (4024) vs build it + finish the run machinery (b4af) is a clean labor split; b4af claims no doc deliverable, 4024 claims no build deliverable.\n- Dependency gap — CLEAN. The doc's content dependency on the eval seam has a real producer in-roster (b4af); the target is not absent. The un-declared sequencing is the ordering finding below.\n- Consumer impact — CLEAN/deferred (code-grounded consumer-impact deferred to E4/G1G2/A1 per the epic's own bright line).\n- Residual references — CLEAN. WS-DOC names WS-EVAL-EXISTING accurately; no stale references to descoped/relocated workstreams (WS-VISUAL-EVAL / WS-MIGRATE et al.) as live siblings.\n- Ordering violation — FINDING (below).\n\nFINDING (G4 · ordering violation):\n- finding: WS-DOC must document the eval seam \"as built\" by WS-EVAL-EXISTING, but no dependency/ordering link sequences the two — WS-DOC could be authored (and closed) before the seam it must mirror is finished, so the doc's eval-seam section can be written against a moving/unbuilt target and silently drift.\n- criteria: [G4]\n- location: child 4024 WS-DOC — Scope bullet \"...how the live tier is triggered + cost/fork-safety rails (reflects WS-EVAL-EXISTING as built)\" and AC4 \"Documents the eval seam: two-tier model, how to author a spec, how the live tier is triggered, cost + fork-safety rails (consistent with WS-EVAL-EXISTING)\"; sibling b4af WS-EVAL-EXISTING AC3/AC4/AC5 (run_eval() live tier, eval-discipline + eval-live tiers BUILT, fork-safety/spend-cap rails).\n- evidence:\n  - WS-DOC explicitly binds its eval-seam documentation to b4af's delivered state: \"reflects WS-EVAL-EXISTING as built\" (Scope) and AC4 \"(consistent with WS-EVAL-EXISTING)\".\n  - The \"as built\" target does not yet exist: per b4af's \"Why\" and the 6f2d SCOPE-DECISION comment, the live tier is presently an unwired stub — run_eval() raises NotImplementedError, deterministic scorer names are inert with no registry, eval-live is a placeholder echo. b4af is the ticket that builds it (Phase 2.1–2.5).\n  - ABSENCE confirmed against the whole roster: neither 4024 nor b4af carries a deps entry (both show \"deps\": []); no depends_on/blocked-by links WS-DOC's authoring to WS-EVAL-EXISTING's completion. Nothing sequences \"document the seam\" after \"build the seam.\"\n- scenarios:\n  - Both open, priority 2, no deps. WS-DOC authored first; cost/fork-safety rails + live-tier trigger mechanics still in flux/stubbed in b4af, so WS-DOC AC4 documents an intended-but-unbuilt design that later drifts from b4af's actual eval-live CI wiring — re-introducing exactly the \"doc out of date\" problem WS-DOC exists to fix.\n  - Conversely, if b4af lands after WS-DOC closes, WS-DOC's \"consistent with WS-EVAL-EXISTING\" AC cannot be truthfully verified at close time (the comparand does not yet exist).\n- impact: Low-to-moderate sequencing risk. Not a contradiction (descriptions agree today), but the cross-child binding is asserted (\"as built\", \"consistent with\") with no ordering link to enforce it, so the doc's eval-seam section can be completed against a moving/unbuilt target and silently drift.\n- checklist_item: Check the 7 cross-child modes — ordering violation.\n- suggested_fix: Add an explicit ordering link so the eval-seam SECTION of WS-DOC follows b4af's eval-live delivery — e.g. a depends_on (or blocked-by) from 4024 → b4af scoped to the eval-seam AC, OR split WS-DOC's eval-seam documentation to land in/immediately after b4af's eval-live CI wiring. If the team intends WS-DOC to be authored first as a design anchor, state that direction explicitly (WS-EVAL-EXISTING implements the seam WS-DOC specifies) and make b4af responsible for reconciling the doc to the as-built rails at its close, giving the \"consistent with WS-EVAL-EXISTING\" AC a defined enforcement point.\n\n(Mirror note: on the b4af pairing, b4af is the producer and carries no independent ordering obligation, so this interaction is owned here and not double-counted there.)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782579813103394001,"uuid":"f16391d2-a5f8-4b85-9b72-7fa1acd58c8e"}